# Keeps the build context small and prevents `COPY . .` in the Dockerfile from
# clobbering the deps stage's freshly-installed node_modules with the host's
# (possibly wrong-platform or stale) copy, and from leaking secrets into an
# image layer.

# Dependencies — reinstalled inside the image, never copied from the host.
node_modules

# Build output — regenerated inside the image; stale host output would be
# copied over the freshly-built one otherwise.
.next
.next/standalone

# Env files — NEVER send real secrets into the build context. Runtime env
# vars are injected via `docker run -e` / compose `environment:`, not baked
# into the image.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Version control
.git
.gitignore

# Editor/OS cruft
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Test artifacts — not needed to build or run the production image.
coverage
playwright-report
test-results
e2e

# Claude Code project files — dev-time only, no runtime relevance.
.claude

# Docs — not needed at runtime; keeps the layer that follows `COPY . .` lean.
*.md
!README.md

# Docker files themselves — no need to send them into their own build context.
Dockerfile
docker-compose*.yml
